<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>救生艇新闻：博客——保护人类</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 12:47:32 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>衰老的人类乳腺图谱揭示了癌症易感性</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/aging-human-breast-atlas-reveals-cancer-susceptibility</link><description>该团队使用先进的成像技术分析了 500 多名 15 岁至 86 岁女性的乳房组织。该组织包括出于非癌症相关原因从女性身上采集的活组织检查。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/aging-human-breast-atlas-reveals-cancer-susceptibility2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 12:47:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/aging-human-breast-atlas-reveals-cancer-susceptibility</guid></item><item><title>Tau 突变导致自噬溶酶体功能障碍</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/tau-mutation-drives-autophagy-lysosome-dysfunction</link><description>研究人员研究了一种名为 tau 的大脑蛋白的特定突变，这种突变会导致该蛋白错误折叠并改变其正常功能。一般来说，当 tau 蛋白错误折叠时，它们会在神经元内积聚，并导致各种形式的痴呆，包括阿尔茨海默氏痴呆和额颞叶痴呆，这是一种与阿尔茨海默氏病类似的神经退行性疾病，通常在中年早期发病，通常会导致认知能力下降之前的人格和行为发生重大变化。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/tau-mutation-drives-autophagy-lysosome-dysfunction2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 12:32:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/tau-mutation-drives-autophagy-lysosome-dysfunction</guid></item><item><title>揭示拓扑绝缘体 Bi2Te3 中非线性霍尔效应的散射贡献</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/unraveling-scattering-contributions-to-the-nonlinear-hall-effect-in-topological-insulator-bi2te3</link><description>研究表明，分布式大脑网络通过动态交互而不是单个中枢来处理语言，这对治疗失语症、脑损伤和认知障碍具有重要意义。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/unraveling-scattering-contributions-to-the-nonlinear-hall-effect-in-topological-insulator-bi2te32.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 12:17:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/unraveling-scattering-contributions-to-the-nonlinear-hall-effect-in-topological-insulator-bi2te3</guid></item><item><title>新研究发现，以身体为中心的走神与更好的心理健康结果相关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/body-focused-mind-wandering-associated-with-better-mental-health-outcomes-finds-new-study</link><description>我们大多数人都经历过，当我们的身体静止并休息时，头脑就不会停止。相反，它开始了自己的旅程，产生关于我们的过去、我们的计划和我们周围的人的想法，这个过程被称为走神。虽然研究人员对这类想法有了很多了解，但并没有太多研究来探索我们的注意力转向内部、转向身体感觉（例如呼吸、心跳或身体感受）的频率。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/body-focused-mind-wandering-associated-with-better-mental-health-outcomes-finds-new-study2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 12:02:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/body-focused-mind-wandering-associated-with-better-mental-health-outcomes-finds-new-study</guid></item><item><title>儿童交替性偏瘫 (AHC) 的最常见原因是如何导致异常复极和心律失常的？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/how-does-the-most-common-cause-of-alternating-hemiplegia-of-childhood-ahc-lead-to-abnormal-repolarization-and-arrhythmogenesis</link><description>Andrew P. Landstrom 及其团队提出了一种 Ca2+ 介导的机制&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/how-does-the-most-common-cause-of-alternating-hemiplegia-of-childhood-ahc-lead-to-abnormal-repolarization-and-arrhythmogenesis2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 11:47:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/how-does-the-most-common-cause-of-alternating-hemiplegia-of-childhood-ahc-lead-to-abnormal-repolarization-and-arrhythmogenesis</guid></item><item><title>Lamin A/C 通过协调染色质可及性和 PCNA 招募来保障复制启动</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/lamin-a-c-safeguards-replication-initiation-by-orchestrating-chromatin-accessibility-and-pcna-recruitment</link><description>张等人。通过影响早期 S 期的染色质组织和 PCNA 可用性，揭示核纤层蛋白 A/C 作为复制启动的看门人。核纤层蛋白 A/C 缺乏会破坏这些控制，增加起始密度和复制依赖性 DNA 损伤。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/lamin-a-c-safeguards-replication-initiation-by-orchestrating-chromatin-accessibility-and-pcna-recruitment2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 11:32:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/lamin-a-c-safeguards-replication-initiation-by-orchestrating-chromatin-accessibility-and-pcna-recruitment</guid></item><item><title>全身麻醉和氯胺酮神经生理学的离散成分</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/general-anesthesia-and-discrete-components-of-ketamine-neurophysiology</link><description>全身麻醉期间使用氯胺酮保留了高频脑电图变化，但缺乏低频调制，这表明氯胺酮的神经生理学成分可以选择性地改变。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/general-anesthesia-and-discrete-components-of-ketamine-neurophysiology2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 11:17:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/general-anesthesia-and-discrete-components-of-ketamine-neurophysiology</guid></item><item><title>为什么抗癌药物总是达不到预期</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/why-anti-cancer-drugs-do-not-always-live-up-to-expectations</link><description>十多年来，一类名为 BET 抑制剂的药物在癌症试验中得到了很高的期望。生物学看起来很有希望。许多癌症依赖于“溴和末端结构域”(BET) 蛋白帮助激活的癌基因，因此阻断 BET 蛋白应该会减缓肿瘤的生长。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/why-anti-cancer-drugs-do-not-always-live-up-to-expectations2.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 11:02:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/why-anti-cancer-drugs-do-not-always-live-up-to-expectations</guid></item><item><title>语言理解源于全脑交流</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/language-understanding-emerges-from-brain-wide-communication</link><description>研究表明，分布式大脑网络通过动态交互而不是单个中枢来处理语言，这对治疗失语症、脑损伤和认知障碍具有重要意义。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/language-understanding-emerges-from-brain-wide-communication.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 10:47:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/language-understanding-emerges-from-brain-wide-communication</guid></item><item><title>插电式太阳能即将到来——它有多危险以及值得吗？</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/plug-in-solar-is-coming-how-dangerous-is-it-and-is-it-worth-it</link><description>插入式太阳能电池板是比专业安装的太阳能电池板更便宜、更简单的替代品。但它们真的能减少能源费用吗？它们安全吗？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/plug-in-solar-is-coming-how-dangerous-is-it-and-is-it-worth-it.jpg" /&gt;</description><pubDate>Fri, 10 Apr 2026 10:32:30 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/plug-in-solar-is-coming-how-dangerous-is-it-and-is-it-worth-it</guid></item></channel></rss>